  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, the considerable time and effort required from participants and organizers can impede the successful execution of participatory design processes.",
    "In response to these challenges, researchers and practitioners have explored various strategies to enhance participatory design by leveraging digital tools to enable more accessible and inclusive participation (Luck, 2018).",
    "The emergence of crowdsourcing technologies has significantly strengthened the trend toward participatory design in recent years (Robertson and Simonsen, 2012; Gooch et al., 2018, Dortheimer et al., 2020).",
    "These technologies facilitate individual communication, thereby relieving political pressure on participants and allowing them to express their opinions freely and, when necessary, anonymously (Dortheimer et al., 2023).",
    "Numerous studies have examined the application of crowdsourcing in architecture and urban design, encompassing ideation (Lu et al., 2018), architectural design (Dortheimer, 2022), co-creation (Mueller et al., 2018; Hofmann et al., 2020), mapping (Borges et al., 2015), and opinion-gathering (Hosio et al., 2015; Wang et al., 2021)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In response to these challenges, researchers and practitioners have explored various strategies to enhance participatory design by leveraging digital tools to enable more accessible and inclusive participation (Luck, 2018).",
